This map documents over 95 massacre sites, villages, and tehsils across Punjab, Jammu & Kashmir (including Mirpur, now in Pakistan-administered Kashmir), and surrounding regions â€” yet this still represents only a fraction of the violence that engulfed the region in 1947. Data is drawn from scholarly works including Ishtiaq Ahmed's "The Punjab Bloodied, Partitioned and Cleansed" (secret British reports), Urvashi Butalia's "The Other Side of Silence" (oral histories), Bal K. Gupta's "Forgotten Atrocities" (Mirpur survivor accounts), and contemporary sources. The true scale of suffering may never be fully known.
